As the world celebrates World Seafarer Day, the department urged young people to explore career opportunities in the maritime sector. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Department of Transport has encouraged young people to consider a career in the maritime sector. As the world celebrates World Seafarer Day, the department urged young people to explore career opportunities at sea. The department’s Dumisani Ntuli said: “In their search for careers, they must explore what the maritime sector has to offer. The maritime sector offers a wide range of opportunities be it imports, on board ships, or in government departments that interact [with the sector].” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)